EPODE I.

This epode was written on the eve of the great engagement be- tween Augustus on one side, and Antony with Cleopatra's forces and ficet on the other. Maecenas had refused to have Horace ac- company him on this expedition, as he had been accustomed to do on similar occasions. The poet feels evidently hurt by the refu- sal. He expresses his anxiety and deep concern.
